 One particle, all 3030 evals to itself   : 76.781
 Thirty particles that never communicate    : 87.383   (random search: 87.433)

 -> Communication is worth +2.499 fitness at ZERO extra cost.
    Without it, thirty searchers are worth no more than random sampling.
    Kennedy & Mendes call this 'wandering cluelessly'; here it is, measured.

 TOPOLOGY: fully connected vs sparse ring (30 paired seeds)
   gbest  mean 89.831  sd 0.317   stagnates at iter 84
   ring   mean 89.961  sd 0.129   stagnates at iter 98
   Wilcoxon on the mean : p = 0.918   NOT significant - the ring does not find a BETTER optimum
   F-test on the spread : 6.0x, p = 6.0e-06   SIGNIFICANT
   -> The ring does not find a better answer. It finds a CONSISTENT one,
      and it is still improving when the fully-connected swarm has quit.
      Kennedy & Mendes (2002): 'greater connectivity speeds up convergence,
      though it does not tend to improve the population's ability to
      discover global optima.' That is what we measure. (They rank the ring
      64th of 70 topologies and recommend von Neumann - see the report.)
